East Frisian Islands

a groupe of german north sea islands.

The east frisian islands are a group of german north sea islands. They are are lined up on the mainland coast of lower saxony, along the east frisian peninsula.

The archipelago stretches for around 90 kilometers from west to east between the mouths of the Ems and Jade or the Wese between 3.5 and 10 kilometers off the mainland.
